From: Sudheesh Mavila <sudheesh.mavila@amd.com>
Date: Mon, 7 Aug 2023 17:17:36 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] amd-xgbe: register has to read twice to get correct value

Link status is latched low, so read once to clear
and then read again to get current state.

 Fixes: 4f3b20bfbb7 ("amd-xgbe: add support for rx-adaptation")
Signed-off-by: Sudheesh Mavila <sudheesh.mavila@amd.com>
Change-Id: I58bdc7c594c03fecb8a84aeae4712035a6c5d209
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/amd/xgbe/xgbe-phy-v2.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/amd/xgbe/xgbe-phy-v2.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/amd/xgbe/xgbe-phy-v2.c
index e07a80229632..13020824d9fb 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/amd/xgbe/xgbe-phy-v2.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/amd/xgbe/xgbe-phy-v2.c
@@ -2937,6 +2937,7 @@ static int xgbe_phy_link_status(struct xgbe_prv_data *pdata, int *an_restart)
 
 		/* check again for the link and adaptation status */
 		reg = XMDIO_READ(pdata, MDIO_MMD_PCS, MDIO_STAT1);
+		reg = XMDIO_READ(pdata, MDIO_MMD_PCS, MDIO_STAT1);
 		if ((reg & MDIO_STAT1_LSTATUS) && pdata->rx_adapt_done)
 			return 1;
 	} else if (reg & MDIO_STAT1_LSTATUS)
